        "heading": "Clinical Note",
        "section_value": "Chief Complaint\nOngoing management of psoriatic arthritis.\nHistory of Present Illness\nThe patient reports ongoing management of psoriatic arthritis. She reports decreasing her prednisone dose and is currently on one dose, which appears to be sufficient. She experienced occasional extra doses due to increased pain in her feet, particularly on days with increased activity. She also reports experiencing adverse effects from a recent COVID vaccine, including significant pain that resolved with a second dose. She notes bruising, which she attributes to prednisone, and reports that these appear without her noticing.\nFindings\nPhysical exam reveals good range of motion in the toes and nails. Examination reveals psoriatic nail changes. No acute findings were noted.\nAssessment\nPsoriatic arthritis.\nPlan\nContinue methotrexate therapy. Discontinue prednisone as previously discussed, monitoring for any flares. Schedule blood work for the next visit. Follow up in three months.",
